data.title: Eisenhower Birthplace State Historic Site, Denison
data.meta_description: Recorded as a Texas Historic Landmark, Eisenhower Birthplace State Historic is an attraction to head to while in the city. The house was the birthplace of the 34th President Dwight D. Eisenhower who also is the first president from the state of Texas. The house was restored by the Eisenhower Foundation in mid 20th Century. It is now under the ownership of the Texas Historical Commission and is listed on the U.S National Register of Historic Places as well as the Texas State Historic Site.
